> Hi I am once again writing in hopes of receiving a response with coherent
> guidance.
>
> Throughout this process I have attempted to provide amulet and the ICF
> with ample information to ensure that networks remain safe, and that our
> team remains in compliance with all guidance and standards.
>
> As previously expressed, we are very happy to follow guidance, however I
> need too strongly express once again we have not received guidance from
> amulet or the ICF.
>
> The only applicable advice has been to form a working group of validators
> on spam, which we have done.
>
> Notional services about 40 chains in cosmos and has contractual
> relationships with probably half of that number. In previous similar
> incidents, we waited.  In one case, this resulted in loss of control of
> funds for one of our customers, Quicksilver. The cosmos hub had a security
> flaw and we didn't tell them.
>
> On the day that we learned this news, we decided that that would never
> happen again.
>
> So we are beginning a lengthy process of distributing to all the teams
> that we work with the fix to this issue.
>
> At the request of Jehan Tremback, a cosmos hub forum post has been made.
>
> The coordination challenge here is absolutely no joe. I am writing,
> requesting assistance with that challenge. I do have stipulations however,
> if Amulet is not willing to take phone calls and wishes to only speak over
> email, I am very sorry but there is not a future for collaboration on
> coordination on security incidents because this incident would not even
> have been discovered, if it weren't for the fact that I spent the past ....
> since August 15.... coordinating the issue.
>
> Coordination in this space does not happen over email.
>
> Thank you for any advice and assistance that you are able to offer
>
> I am in Istanbul and I am available to meet with any relevant party in
> person and demo the issue. Unless of course I don't trust them in which
> case I would not show them this.
